body_html:
@gunan What I mean is that we've been able to build TensorFlow on TX1 since 1.4.0. 1.8.0-rc0 was the first to break.

If TX1 is not officially supported, then surely Raspberry Pi is (if it's part of the nightlies)? I agree with @jessebenson - it looks like the same issue. Would it be easier for you to investigate it there? I could help you then test across other aarch64 platforms I have access to (TX1, HiKey960, RK3399)?
